===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|writen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term/t|ang|wrītan||to incise, engrave, write, draw, bestow by writing}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*wrītaną||to carve, write}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*wrey-||to rip, tear}}. Cognate with {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|write||to wear by rubbing, rip, tear|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|wrijten||to argue, quarrel|lang=nl}}, Dutch {{term|rijten||to rip, tear|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|wrieten|lang=nds}}, {{term|rieten||to tear, split|lang=nds}}, German {{term|reißen||to tear, rip|lang=de}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|rita||to draw, design, delineate, model|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|ríta||to cut, scratch, write|lang=is}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|ritzen||to carve, scratch|lang=de}}.

